{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pizza Base","content":["Place Parmesan in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>15 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place cauliflower in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer cauliflower to simmering basket and insert into mixing bowl.","Add boiling water and cook <nobr>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, preheat oven to <strong>200°C<\/strong>.","Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and discard any water left in mixing bowl. Run simmering basket under cold water to cool cooked cauliflower. Place cauliflower on a clean, dry tea towel, then holding tea towel over a bowl, squeeze into a ball to remove as much liquid as possible.","Place cooked, drained cauliflower, eggs, dried oregano, garlic powder, salt, pepper and 35 g reserved grated Parmesan in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Transfer mixture to a baking tray lined with baking paper, and using a spatula, form into a flat circle (approx. Ø 30cm). Bake for 10 minutes (200°C), then remove from oven, flip pizza base over, and bake for a further 10 minutes (200°C). Meanwhile, make pizza toppings."]},{"title":"Pizza Toppings","content":["Place onion, garlic and oil in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <nobr>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add passata, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper, then place simmering basket instead of measuring cup on mixing bowl lid and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Spread sauce over cooked pizza base, then add mozzarella and pepperoni. Finish with reserved Parmesan, and bake for a further 10 minutes until top is golden and bubbling."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pizza Base","content":["50 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (3 cm)","1 cauliflower, cut in pieces (approx. 600 g)","500 g boiling water","2 medium eggs, beaten","1 tsp dried oregano","1 tsp garlic powder","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper"]},{"title":"Pizza Toppings","content":["½ onion, quartered (approx. 55 g)","1 clove garlic","20 g olive oil","180 g passata","1 tsp dried oregano","½ tsp sugar","½ tsp fine sea salt","1 pinch ground black pepper","100 g mozzarella, sliced","8 slices pepperoni sausage (approx. 140 g)"]}],"id":"r211198","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-aKJ-jYQ_by0\/XZWYdMnuSRI\/AAAAAAAAd-Q\/WAqDmeP0VeAHyVhLpYwlutiL-90Fu8gpwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_AMgo6XklhVzfopZx.png","title":"Cauliflower Crust Pizza","publishedAt":"2017-07-31T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"15.6 g","fat":"18.3 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"4.4 g","calories":"1069 kJ \/ 257 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tea towel, baking tray and paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["For a strong, firm crust, it's important to squeeze as much liquid as possible out of the cooked cauliflower before the other ingredients are added.","This delicious pizza uses cauliflower as a base, resulting in a low-carb alternative to the traditional dish.","Try replacing the pepperoni with cooked chicken and a drizzle of barbecue sauce, or slices of Parma ham followed by a handful of rocket once cooked."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","1h 20m","8 slices"]}